theorem P1_implies_closure_interior_closure_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  intro hP1
  -- `closure (interior (closure A))` is always contained in `closure A`
  have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
    have : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  -- Rewrite `closure A` via `P1` and obtain the reverse inclusion
  have h_cl_eq : closure A = closure (interior A) :=
    (Topology.P1_iff_closure_eq_closure_interior (X := X) (A := A)).1 hP1
  have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
    have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) := by
      have h_sub : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) :=
        interior_mono (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A)
      exact closure_mono h_sub
    simpa [h_cl_eq] using this
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem closure_interior_closure_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
  have h : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := interior_subset
  exact closure_mono h

theorem interior_closure_subset_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure A) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, `x` belongs to the closure of `A`.
  have hx_closureA : x ∈ closure A := interior_subset hx
  -- Since `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`, taking closures gives
  -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h_subset : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have h : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := subset_closure
    exact closure_mono h
  -- Combining the two facts yields the desired membership.
  exact h_subset hx_closureA

theorem denseInterior_implies_P3 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (interior A)) : Topology.P3 A := by
  -- We must show `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`.
  dsimp [Topology.P3]
  intro x hxA
  -- Since `interior A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h_cl : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa using hDense.closure_eq
  -- Therefore, the interior of that closure is also the whole space.
  have h_int_univ : interior (closure (interior A)) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [h_cl, interior_univ]
  -- In particular, `x` lies in this interior.
  have hx_int : x ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
    simpa [h_int_univ] using (Set.mem_univ x)
  -- Monotonicity of closure (and interior) yields the desired inclusion.
  have h_mono : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
    exact interior_mono this
  exact h_mono hx_int

theorem interior_closure_mono {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : A ⊆ B) : interior (closure A) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  have h_closure : closure A ⊆ closure B := closure_mono hAB
  exact interior_mono h_closure
